{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7TdRfWT4uoXXkF3Qvq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Both tests pass.\n\n**The bug** (`src/money.js`): `orderTotalCents` rounded the discount **per line** and then summed, but the spec says the discount applies to the **order subtotal** and is rounded **once**. Rounding each line up can accumulate an extra cent.\n\n**Concrete case:** an order subtotal of 999¢ at 10% off is 999 × 0.9 = 899.1¢ → **$8.99**. Split across lines (e.g. 555¢ and 444¢), per-line rounding gave 500 + 400 = **$9.00** — exactly the off-by-one billing reported.\n\n**The fix:** sum all lines into the integer subtotal first, then apply the discount and `Math.round` a single time. This also fixes `invoiceFor` and `renderTotal`, which both delegate to this function."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":317,"cache_read_input_tokens":25155,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":317},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"acdc58f6-fd9b-4b39-977c-f509c31c50bb","uuid":"5648ab32-69bd-4914-9f57-eb60fd9d01a9","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:40:47.322Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7TaX39qP146de9JwsF"}
